 2017-16892017-12-15,  ,  ,  ,  INAC
ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectGordons Indian Reserve No. 86, Saskatchewan ** Confirmation **
PrecisOrder requested to confirm that the lands described on a plan of survey recorded in Canada Land Survey Records as Plan No. T299 CLSR SK were set apart as reserve for the use and benefit of GEORGE GORDON FIRST NATION, and that the lands have been set apart for that purpose in Saskatchewan, since July 14, 1899. The lands are located in the Rural Municipality of Touchwood No. 248, in Saskatchewan.
